


lyap(G)                        Scilab Function                        lyap(G)






NAME
  lyap  - Lyapunov equation

CALLING SEQUENCE
  [X]=lyap(A,C,'c')
  [X]=lyap(A,C,'d')

PARAMETERS
  A, C      : real square matrices, C must be symmetric

DESCRIPTION
  X = lyap(A,C,flag) solves the continuous time or discrete time  matrix
  Lyapunov matrix equation:
  A'*X + X*A = C       ( flag='c' )
  A'*X*A - X = C       ( flag='d' )

SEE ALSO
  sylv






































